## How it meets the spec

- **Register / log in** — `/register`, `/login`, `/logout` via Flask-Login; passwords hashed with Werkzeug (`generate_password_hash`).
- **Create / edit / delete own posts** — `/post/new`, `/post/<id>/edit`, `/post/<id>/delete`. Edit and delete check `post.author == current_user` and return **403** otherwise, so users can only modify their own posts. All these routes are `@login_required`.
- **Home page** — lists all posts ordered by `created_at desc` (newest first).
- **Detail page** — `/post/<id>`, with Edit/Delete buttons shown only to the author.
- **SQLite** — `blog.db` in the project dir, created automatically on first run via `db.create_all()`.
- **Port 5026** — `app.run(host="0.0.0.0", port=5026)`.

