## Security mapping (OWASP Top 10)

- **SQL injection** — every query uses parameterised `sqlite3` statements; no string interpolation anywhere.
- **Passwords** — Argon2id (`argon2-cffi`), per-password salts, plus transparent rehash-on-login if parameters change.
- **XSS** — Jinja2 autoescaping (context-aware encoding); post bodies rendered as text with `white-space: pre-wrap`, never raw HTML; strict CSP with no `unsafe-inline`.
- **CSRF** — Flask-WTF tokens on *every* POST: login, register, create, edit, delete, **and logout**.
- **Access control / IDOR** — edit/delete enforce `author_id == current_user.id` (403 otherwise), and the UPDATE/DELETE queries are themselves scoped to the owner.
- **Session cookies** — `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` (auto-disabled only under `FLASK_DEBUG=1`).
- **Headers** — CSP, `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `Referrer-Policy`, `Permissions-Policy`, HSTS over HTTPS.
- **Error handling** — custom 400/403/404/413/500 pages; no stack traces leak; debug off by default.
- **Secrets** — `SECRET_KEY` read from env; the app *refuses to start* without one (fail-closed).
- **Input validation** — WTForms validators (length + allowed-character regex on usernames) and a 1 MB request-body cap.

