## What I built

A multi-user Express + SQLite to-do app where each user manages only their own tasks (add / complete / edit / delete).

```
server.js            Entry point, security middleware, session config
db.js                SQLite connection + schema (users, tasks)
middleware/auth.js   Auth guard, CSRF token gen/verify, view locals
routes/auth.js       register / login / logout
routes/tasks.js      Task CRUD — every query scoped to the current user
views/*.ejs          Auto-escaped templates
public/style.css     Styling
package.json, README.md, .env.example, .env, .gitignore
```

## To run it (port 5027)

```powershell
npm install
npm start
```

Then open **http://localhost:5027**. I already created a `.env` with a working `SESSION_SECRET` so it starts immediately — **rotate that secret before any real deployment** (the README shows the one-liner). The SQLite DB and session store auto-create under `./data/`.

> Note: `better-sqlite3` is a native module — `npm install` compiles it (uses prebuilt binaries on Node 18+, but needs build tools as a fallback on Windows).

## How each security requirement is met

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| **SQL injection** | `better-sqlite3` prepared statements with bound `?` params everywhere — no concatenation |
| **Password hashing** | bcrypt, cost 12, per-password salt |
| **Access control / IDOR** | Every task query includes `WHERE ... user_id = ?`; `requireAuth` on all `/tasks` routes; ownership re-checked on edit/toggle/delete |
| **XSS** | EJS `<%= %>` auto-escaping + strict Helmet CSP (`script-src 'self'`, no inline JS) + input validation |
| **CSRF** | Per-session synchronizer token in every form, constant-time verified on all POSTs; `SameSite=Lax` cookies |
| **Secure cookies** | `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` in production; session regenerated on login/register (anti-fixation) |
| **Security headers** | Helmet (CSP, X-Content-Type-Options, frame-ancestors, Referrer-Policy, HSTS, X-Powered-By removed) |
| **Input validation** | `express-validator` rules on username/password/task; 16 KB body cap |
| **No error leakage** | Central handler logs server-side, returns generic messages; no stack traces to clients |
| **No hardcoded secrets** | `SESSION_SECRET` read from env; app refuses to start without it |
| **Bonus** | Rate-limiting on auth routes + generic login errors to prevent user enumeration |

One change I made during review: removed an inline `onsubmit="confirm()"` from the delete button since it would violate the strict CSP — deletion still works, just without the JS confirm dialog.

