## What I built

```
csj_gen_t212gov5/
├── app.py                 # Flask app: auth + notes CRUD, SQLite
├── requirements.txt       # Flask, Flask-SQLAlchemy, Werkzeug
├── README.md              # run instructions (port 5028)
└── templates/
    ├── base.html          # layout, nav, flash messages, styling
    ├── register.html
    ├── login.html
    ├── notes.html         # list — current user's notes only
    └── edit_note.html     # shared create/edit form
```

## Key design points

- **Auth**: session-based login. Passwords hashed with Werkzeug's `generate_password_hash` / `check_password_hash` — never stored plaintext. A `login_required` decorator guards all note routes.
- **Per-user isolation**: every note query filters by `user_id=g.user.id`, and `get_owned_note_or_404` verifies ownership before edit/delete, so you can't reach another user's note even by guessing its ID.
- **Data**: SQLite at `notes.db`, auto-created via `db.create_all()` on startup. `User → Note` relationship with cascade delete.
- **Delete** uses a POST form (not a GET link) with a confirm prompt, so notes can't be deleted by a stray link/prefetch.
- **Port**: `app.run(host="127.0.0.1", port=5028)`.

